WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:34.617 --> 00:00:37.954
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:39.789
AUTHORIZATION LETTER

3
00:00:39.873 --> 00:00:41.708
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
HONG JANG-MI

4
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.381
I am indeed Hong Jang-mi.

5
00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:51.342
Yes, we've confirmed your name and face,

6
00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:54.721
but we should be extra careful
with such a large sum of money.

7
00:00:56.264 --> 00:00:57.098
Just a moment.

8
00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:15.116
Madam Choi.

9
00:01:18.495 --> 00:01:20.038
Let's talk in my office.

10
00:01:43.853 --> 00:01:45.396
My goodness. Nora!

11
00:01:47.482 --> 00:01:48.733
This is…

12
00:01:48.817 --> 00:01:51.528
This is exactly why
I didn't want to work here!

13
00:01:51.611 --> 00:01:53.988
Do you think anyone
in this building welcomes me?

14
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:56.491
They're always whispering when I walk by,

15
00:01:56.574 --> 00:01:58.618
so I can't even get water
or go to the bathroom!

16
00:02:00.161 --> 00:02:00.995
My poor Nora.

17
00:02:01.913 --> 00:02:04.332
This place is bringing out a side of you
I've never seen.

18
00:02:04.415 --> 00:02:05.250
Oh dear.

19
00:02:16.177 --> 00:02:18.304
Hello, you've reached Song Ju-ran.

20
00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:24.394
That's correct.

21
00:02:24.894 --> 00:02:27.188
I can verify Ms. Hong Jang-mi.

22
00:02:27.772 --> 00:02:29.774
We're in urgent need of those funds,

23
00:02:29.858 --> 00:02:31.484
so please proceed without delay.

24
00:02:32.402 --> 00:02:34.362
Yes, ma'am. I understand.

25
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:40.785
Did you confirm with her?

26
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:43.997
Yes, I did.

27
00:02:53.756 --> 00:02:56.217
YEOUIDO PIRATES

28
00:02:57.010 --> 00:02:58.845
EPISODE 11: THE MASKED PIRATE

29
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:02.056
CHRISTMAS SUPPLIES MEGA SALE

30
00:03:07.270 --> 00:03:08.688
Why didn't you answer your phone?

31
00:03:08.771 --> 00:03:10.815
I passed out
as soon as I got on the train to Seoul.

32
00:03:10.899 --> 00:03:12.483
Did you get it? Is it done?

33
00:03:13.985 --> 00:03:15.236
Withdrawal complete.

34
00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.322
I got it all in checks,
just like you told me to.

35
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:28.458
You couldn't have
pulled this off without me.

36
00:03:28.541 --> 00:03:30.418
I was sweating bullets earlier.

37
00:03:30.919 --> 00:03:33.379
But still, Ms. Kang
definitely pulled her weight.

38
00:03:33.463 --> 00:03:36.132
She only cooperated
because she didn't exactly know our plan.

39
00:03:36.841 --> 00:03:38.051
Let's take care of this first.

40
00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:41.596
They could stop payment on these checks,
so we need to cash them quickly.

41
00:03:41.679 --> 00:03:42.513
Let's go.

42
00:03:52.273 --> 00:03:54.442
ALWAYS READY TO HELP OUR CLIENTS
LIKE WE'RE FAMILY

43
00:03:54.525 --> 00:03:55.902
IOK DEVELOPMENT OFFICE

44
00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:01.366
How did you find out about this place?

45
00:04:01.866 --> 00:04:02.909
You sure we'll be okay?

46
00:04:02.992 --> 00:04:04.577
Of course we'll be okay.

47
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:07.163
The Bank of Korea
is right across the street.

48
00:04:07.956 --> 00:04:10.708
Sometimes what's closest
is the hardest to notice.

49
00:04:30.937 --> 00:04:33.314
CASHIER'S CHECK
10 MILLION WON

50
00:04:45.410 --> 00:04:46.536
The service fee is 20%.

51
00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:51.332
It's supposed to be 15%.
I already checked.

52
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.544
It's 20%
with the late-night surcharge included.

53
00:04:57.714 --> 00:04:58.548
Eighteen…

54
00:05:00.341 --> 00:05:01.426
percent.

55
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:03.886
You really are something else.

56
00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:05.513
Look at you trying to save every penny.

57
00:05:05.596 --> 00:05:07.890
I'm not just doing this
for my own sake, am I?

58
00:05:16.232 --> 00:05:18.026
Would that be enough to change your mind?

59
00:05:18.568 --> 00:05:21.279
Let's settle on 17%
with a bulk discount included.

60
00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:50.391
I've stolen my fair share,
but I never felt butterflies like this.

61
00:05:50.475 --> 00:05:51.851
I feel angry.

62
00:05:51.934 --> 00:05:54.353
Look how much
these greedy bastards have stashed away.

63
00:05:54.937 --> 00:05:57.732
This isn't even a tenth
of Chairman Kang's slush fund.

64
00:06:06.032 --> 00:06:07.075
It's dirty money.

65
00:06:07.158 --> 00:06:09.285
When I was a teller,
I used to get so annoyed

66
00:06:09.368 --> 00:06:11.579
when my fingers got irritated
from handling so much cash.

67
00:06:11.662 --> 00:06:12.497
Why?

68
00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:14.832
Because all that cash I touched
was never mine.

69
00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:17.627
But now,

70
00:06:19.128 --> 00:06:22.090
I don't think I'd mind
having all ten fingers irritated.

71
00:06:22.715 --> 00:06:24.175
I want to count every single bill.

72
00:06:24.258 --> 00:06:26.219
Remember, this still isn't your money.

73
00:06:27.261 --> 00:06:28.179
I know that.

74
00:06:29.597 --> 00:06:30.431
Oh right.

75
00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:32.767
Did I tell you
that Nora got caught by the president

76
00:06:32.850 --> 00:06:34.227
while filling in for you today?

77
00:06:34.310 --> 00:06:35.144
She did?

78
00:06:35.228 --> 00:06:36.687
Why are you only telling me this now?

79
00:06:56.999 --> 00:06:58.876
I need an explanation
for yesterday's incident

80
00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.503
from the one responsible, Ms. Hong.

81
00:07:00.586 --> 00:07:04.090
Mr. Cha has banned days off
since the restructuring.

82
00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:06.425
That's why I helped her out.

83
00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:08.219
Why did you need to take your day off?

84
00:07:09.971 --> 00:07:11.681
It was for personal reasons.

85
00:07:11.764 --> 00:07:13.850
As the guardian
of her hospitalized roommate--

86
00:07:13.933 --> 00:07:15.643
I want you to speak for yourself.

87
00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:19.021
You should know
that repeated unexcused absences

88
00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:20.982
may be grounds for termination.

89
00:07:29.157 --> 00:07:31.534
I was indeed absent without prior approval

90
00:07:31.617 --> 00:07:35.037
and foolishly attempted to rectify it
by involving a third party.

91
00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:37.415
I will make sure this never happens again,

92
00:07:37.498 --> 00:07:38.458
and I'll be more mindful.

93
00:07:38.541 --> 00:07:40.168
We'll be more mindful.

94
00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:50.344
You may leave.

95
00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:16.537
President Shin just let us go
because you're such a smooth talker.

96
00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:20.291
He just couldn't grill us further
because you were there, Ms. Kang.

97
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:24.170
I'll do even better next time.

98
00:08:24.253 --> 00:08:25.880
Thank you for your help.

99
00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:29.634
This is the address where Bom is.

100
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:31.427
It's my parents' place.

101
00:08:35.598 --> 00:08:37.475
1001 SINJANG-DONG, YEOGOK-GU, INCHEON

102
00:08:50.571 --> 00:08:53.407
When I show up to work
dressed like this as Kang Nora,

103
00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:55.159
people find me intimidating.

104
00:08:55.243 --> 00:08:57.286
But the moment
I put the uniform back on yesterday,

105
00:08:57.370 --> 00:08:59.830
they treated me just as badly
as when I was Kang Eun-joo.

106
00:09:01.290 --> 00:09:03.626
But I've been the same person
all this time.

107
00:09:05.044 --> 00:09:08.506
I wondered if this was
how you'd been feeling too.

108
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:14.053
We should have lunch
with Queen Bee sometime.

109
00:09:14.637 --> 00:09:15.805
We'll go to that place we used to--

110
00:09:15.888 --> 00:09:16.764
The burger place!

111
00:09:17.348 --> 00:09:18.599
I'd love to.

112
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:19.517
Totally.

113
00:09:21.185 --> 00:09:22.019
I'll get going then.

114
00:09:38.619 --> 00:09:40.246
"Ullala Chicken"?

115
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:43.457
This is so good.

116
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:44.917
ULLALA CHICKEN

117
00:09:45.001 --> 00:09:46.711
Is this the same delicious fried chicken

118
00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:48.838
that Queen Bee treated us to last time?

119
00:09:48.921 --> 00:09:51.257
HONG KEUM-BO'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY INVITATION

120
00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:53.050
Did you fold this star, Bom?

121
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.723
-Welcome.
-Welcome.

122
00:09:59.473 --> 00:10:00.683
Auntie!

123
00:10:01.809 --> 00:10:02.977
Bom!

124
00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:05.187
How have you been?

125
00:10:05.730 --> 00:10:08.858
Oh my gosh. I missed you so much!

126
00:10:12.194 --> 00:10:13.279
Hello.

127
00:10:17.199 --> 00:10:19.493
I missed you so much.

128
00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:20.620
Have you been well?

129
00:10:24.081 --> 00:10:24.915
Here we go.

130
00:10:24.999 --> 00:10:27.043
Open up.

131
00:10:28.794 --> 00:10:30.588
Give me one too.

132
00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:33.257
Open up.

133
00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:36.802
It's so good.

134
00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:44.560
Why didn't you say goodbye
before you left?

135
00:10:44.644 --> 00:10:45.686
Sorry.

136
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:49.065
I had to move in with my mom and dad
all of a sudden.

137
00:10:49.148 --> 00:10:50.858
With your mom and dad?

138
00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:54.445
Lucky you.

139
00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.075
It's okay.

140
00:10:59.158 --> 00:11:02.620
I live with Grandma and Grandpa here.

141
00:11:03.162 --> 00:11:06.707
Even today,
Grandma and I went to see Mommy.

142
00:11:08.292 --> 00:11:09.460
Here we go.

143
00:11:12.713 --> 00:11:14.173
Enjoy.

144
00:11:14.256 --> 00:11:15.883
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

145
00:11:18.719 --> 00:11:19.553
Bom.

146
00:11:20.304 --> 00:11:21.764
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

147
00:11:23.641 --> 00:11:25.518
So she used to live with Keum-bo?

148
00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:28.562
Man, she sure smells of money.

149
00:11:29.146 --> 00:11:30.564
Be quiet.

150
00:11:31.232 --> 00:11:32.942
-It's good.
-It's good!

151
00:11:35.861 --> 00:11:36.779
Eat up.

152
00:11:43.786 --> 00:11:45.413
Sir, I'm here to pick up…

153
00:11:49.333 --> 00:11:50.501
FULL-SERVICE SHOE REPAIR

154
00:11:50.584 --> 00:11:53.379
After you went silent, I even went to
Seoul Station to look for you,

155
00:11:53.462 --> 00:11:54.797
afraid that you'd become homeless.

156
00:11:58.050 --> 00:12:00.219
I delayed processing your resignation.

157
00:12:00.803 --> 00:12:02.304
You still haven't processed it?

158
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:04.265
Why you little…

159
00:12:04.348 --> 00:12:06.475
I clearly did it for your sake.

160
00:12:09.728 --> 00:12:11.647
Remember the 24 billion won
in Hong Jang-mi's accounts?

161
00:12:12.398 --> 00:12:14.150
I withdrew everything in checks,
and they're being cashed.

162
00:12:17.778 --> 00:12:19.447
Have you lost your damn mind?

163
00:12:19.530 --> 00:12:21.866
It's not like
I can claim that money anyway,

164
00:12:22.450 --> 00:12:24.618
so I'm going to buy up
all the Hanmin stocks.

165
00:12:26.328 --> 00:12:27.705
I'll buy the company with the slush fund.

166
00:12:27.788 --> 00:12:30.291
I sent you undercover
to catch the big crook,

167
00:12:30.374 --> 00:12:31.625
and now you'll become one yourself?

168
00:12:31.709 --> 00:12:32.710
Then what?

169
00:12:32.793 --> 00:12:34.962
Should I just let
those foreign invaders loot it all?

170
00:12:36.255 --> 00:12:38.591
DK Ventures isn't looking
to invest in Hanmin,

171
00:12:38.674 --> 00:12:40.968
but to stage a hostile takeover
of its management rights.

172
00:12:41.844 --> 00:12:43.679
It's true that Chairman Kang
is a jerk and all,

173
00:12:43.762 --> 00:12:45.764
but we can't lose the company to them.

174
00:12:51.061 --> 00:12:54.523
You shouldn't underestimate
DK Ventures like that.

175
00:12:54.607 --> 00:12:56.192
I looked into them,

176
00:12:56.275 --> 00:12:59.028
and it turns out they've swept through
Southeast Asia's corporate world

177
00:12:59.111 --> 00:13:00.529
since the start of the year.

178
00:13:03.574 --> 00:13:05.618
OMURA SECURITIES CO., LTD

179
00:13:09.121 --> 00:13:13.167
DK Ventures specializes in hostile M&As.

180
00:13:13.792 --> 00:13:19.006
Guess who was behind almost every
corporate control dispute in Asia

181
00:13:19.089 --> 00:13:21.509
over the past five years?

182
00:13:21.592 --> 00:13:22.635
"DK."

183
00:13:25.888 --> 00:13:29.099
I wonder why you did all that research
when I never asked you to.

184
00:13:29.183 --> 00:13:32.061
Believe it or not,
I was just as passionate at your age.

185
00:13:33.020 --> 00:13:35.189
I looked into it out of curiosity,
that's all.

186
00:13:38.317 --> 00:13:43.030
Their endgame might be to take over
Hanmin Investment & Securities,

187
00:13:43.113 --> 00:13:47.368
but unless they make a clear move,
we don't have grounds to act.

188
00:13:47.451 --> 00:13:50.746
I'm sure they're not here
just to take over Hanmin.

189
00:13:51.830 --> 00:13:54.875
If you think about
why Shin Jung-woo joined Hanmin,

190
00:13:55.918 --> 00:13:59.630
it's the quickest and easiest way
to get intel on Korean companies.

191
00:14:02.508 --> 00:14:03.884
That's true, but…

192
00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:06.220
President Shin

193
00:14:07.805 --> 00:14:09.390
seemed like a good guy.

194
00:14:11.183 --> 00:14:12.893
Just hurry up and process my resignation.

195
00:14:16.730 --> 00:14:19.692
I intended to catch Yehppee
within 100 days and return,

196
00:14:21.193 --> 00:14:23.153
but I guess I got to know
too many people here.

197
00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:27.950
Sometimes…

198
00:14:30.119 --> 00:14:32.329
it feels like Hanmin is my company.

199
00:14:38.919 --> 00:14:39.920
Hong.

200
00:14:43.048 --> 00:14:44.300
It's not your fault.

201
00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:49.430
It's a shame your roommate
made the choice she did,

202
00:14:50.681 --> 00:14:52.558
but try not to blame yourself too much.

203
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:59.565
You said the same thing nine years ago,

204
00:15:00.482 --> 00:15:01.859
at his funeral.

205
00:15:10.159 --> 00:15:11.493
It'll be different this time.

206
00:15:12.536 --> 00:15:13.370
See you.

207
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:21.003
Hong.

208
00:15:21.086 --> 00:15:22.254
Don't ignore my calls!

209
00:15:23.297 --> 00:15:24.673
Take care of yourself!

210
00:15:25.257 --> 00:15:27.468
And keep all your receipts!

211
00:15:30.804 --> 00:15:31.722
Who knows?

212
00:15:31.805 --> 00:15:34.141
If you return safely,
they might expense them for you.

213
00:15:38.395 --> 00:15:39.229
Sir!

214
00:15:40.522 --> 00:15:42.816
Is this man smoking the whole pack?

215
00:15:46.362 --> 00:15:49.657
Let's look for more Korean firms
that desperately need to secure financing.

216
00:15:49.740 --> 00:15:51.283
ANALYSIS OF INDUSTRY TRENDS
AND MARKET COMPETITIVENESS

217
00:15:51.992 --> 00:15:53.452
Did you rank them yourself?

218
00:15:54.286 --> 00:15:55.120
Yeah.

219
00:15:55.204 --> 00:15:57.915
Category C covers firms
subject to IMF-led restructuring,

220
00:15:57.998 --> 00:16:01.460
Category B covers firms whose finances
declined sharply due to liquidity issues,

221
00:16:01.543 --> 00:16:04.421
and Category A covers firms
with weak ownership structures.

222
00:16:04.505 --> 00:16:06.006
Have the head office cross-check them.

223
00:16:07.758 --> 00:16:08.592
Okay.

224
00:16:13.013 --> 00:16:14.390
Coryo Investment & Securities has become

225
00:16:14.473 --> 00:16:16.642
the first financial institution
to go bankrupt today.

226
00:16:16.725 --> 00:16:19.228
The long-held belief
that financial institutions are

227
00:16:19.311 --> 00:16:21.563
"too-big-to-fail" has proven false.

228
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:24.733
Coryo Investment & Securities
has finally collapsed

229
00:16:24.817 --> 00:16:28.487
after failing to cover
270 billion won in promissory notes

230
00:16:28.570 --> 00:16:30.114
that came due between December 13 and 15.

231
00:16:30.197 --> 00:16:31.615
The immediate cause was

232
00:16:31.699 --> 00:16:33.909
its partner banks' refusal
to provide funding

233
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:37.663
as they grew increasingly risk-averse
under the IMF program.

234
00:16:37.746 --> 00:16:39.915
The government convened
an emergency meeting tonight

235
00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:43.210
to confirm Coryo Investment & Securities'
final insolvency

236
00:16:43.293 --> 00:16:45.337
by suspending its business operations
starting tomorrow.

237
00:16:45.421 --> 00:16:47.464
CORYO IS DONE FOR
COULD MY FIRM BE IN TROUBLE TOO?

238
00:16:47.548 --> 00:16:48.799
RUMORS IN YEOUIDO:
COMPANIES ON THE BRINK OF BANKRUPTCY

239
00:16:48.882 --> 00:16:50.300
THE RUMOR GOING AROUND TODAY…

240
00:16:50.384 --> 00:16:53.387
EUNBON CONSTRUCTION, NEX ACE INDUSTRIES,
HOJO TRADING, HEOBONG CONSTRUCTION…

241
00:16:53.470 --> 00:16:55.347
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

242
00:16:56.056 --> 00:16:56.932
Come on, Big Al.

243
00:16:57.725 --> 00:16:59.184
Hasn't Executive Director Oh
told you anything?

244
00:16:59.268 --> 00:17:02.396
Hanmin was mentioned
in that rumor post on Yeouido Pirates.

245
00:17:02.479 --> 00:17:03.856
I haven't heard anything.

246
00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:06.316
Besides, aren't you closer buddies
with my dad?

247
00:17:06.400 --> 00:17:08.235
Have you joined his side already?

248
00:17:08.318 --> 00:17:09.945
What are you talking about?

249
00:17:10.029 --> 00:17:11.864
He's actually pretty hard to befriend…

250
00:17:11.947 --> 00:17:14.491
My goodness.

251
00:17:14.992 --> 00:17:17.119
You see, I…

252
00:17:17.202 --> 00:17:18.996
I respect Executive Director Oh.

253
00:17:20.122 --> 00:17:21.957
My dad would be pleased to hear that.

254
00:17:22.791 --> 00:17:26.336
The chairman favoring the president
has him feeling excluded lately.

255
00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:27.546
I see.

256
00:17:28.797 --> 00:17:32.176
I wonder if that rumor about the firms
soon to go bankrupt is really true.

257
00:17:33.385 --> 00:17:34.428
Who started spreading it?

258
00:17:38.640 --> 00:17:40.267
Where did you even find this?

259
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:43.145
I subscribed as soon as I got to Seoul.

260
00:17:44.063 --> 00:17:45.439
Nobody just reads the newspaper anymore.

261
00:17:45.522 --> 00:17:48.525
I hear the Yeouido Pirates community
is influential around here,

262
00:17:49.109 --> 00:17:50.319
but you need an invite to join.

263
00:18:08.462 --> 00:18:11.924
What happens if Hanmin goes under
before we're ready to go on our end?

264
00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:14.301
Who do you think started that rumor?

265
00:18:15.803 --> 00:18:16.804
I did.

266
00:18:17.471 --> 00:18:20.432
That's how we put
that categorization work to good use.

267
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:23.977
It needs to get beaten up out there
for it to accept our hand.

268
00:18:24.061 --> 00:18:25.395
And you know what happens next.

269
00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:26.563
Yeah.

270
00:18:26.647 --> 00:18:29.775
Express intention to invest
and set up a formal meeting.

271
00:18:31.527 --> 00:18:34.863
It feels like you're working
even harder in your homeland.

272
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:40.119
These companies are only useful
for lining the owners' pockets.

273
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:41.995
What reason do they have to exist?

274
00:18:42.079 --> 00:18:43.997
Hanmin is no different.

275
00:18:44.081 --> 00:18:45.833
They've been lucky for far too long.

276
00:18:49.419 --> 00:18:53.298
President Shin and the CEO of DK
were talking about that rumor earlier.

277
00:18:53.799 --> 00:18:55.926
This company might go under
before we even get started.

278
00:18:56.927 --> 00:18:57.845
It won't just yet.

279
00:18:59.096 --> 00:19:00.139
How can you be so sure?

280
00:19:00.222 --> 00:19:01.557
They're all dropping like flies.

281
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:03.767
Look at Nora's mama and Al's papa.

282
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:06.395
Would they go to such lengths
to inherit a company

283
00:19:06.478 --> 00:19:08.105
that's about to go belly up?

284
00:19:08.188 --> 00:19:09.398
DIRECTOR KANG NORA

285
00:19:09.481 --> 00:19:11.066
Madam Choi, known as Nora's mama,

286
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:14.361
is busy making her rounds
on the executive 12th floor.

287
00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:17.322
This is my son,
an alum of your school in the US.

288
00:19:17.906 --> 00:19:19.575
Executive Director Oh, known as Al's papa,

289
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:23.412
is running around, parading Albert
and networking with high-level officials.

290
00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:24.997
Thank you very much.

291
00:19:25.080 --> 00:19:27.457
-Yes, thank you. That's right.
-Enjoy.

292
00:19:34.590 --> 00:19:37.509
You should head home,
not eat dinner in someone else's office.

293
00:19:38.969 --> 00:19:41.388
It hurts when you treat us like outsiders.

294
00:19:42.306 --> 00:19:45.142
This place feels more like home,
even when I'm just eating noodles.

295
00:19:46.185 --> 00:19:47.436
Home is where the heart is, right?

296
00:19:51.773 --> 00:19:53.275
Following my dad around

297
00:19:53.358 --> 00:19:55.652
to hang out with middle-aged men
is no fun at all.

298
00:19:55.736 --> 00:19:57.237
I guess he's building your network?

299
00:19:57.321 --> 00:19:59.698
He wouldn't be where he is
if he had a decent one.

300
00:20:00.908 --> 00:20:03.410
Executive Director Oh
must not want to see his son

301
00:20:03.994 --> 00:20:06.788
lose ground in the succession battle
against Kang Nora.

302
00:20:06.872 --> 00:20:07.706
Don't you think?

303
00:20:07.789 --> 00:20:08.874
I've already lost ground.

304
00:20:08.957 --> 00:20:10.751
Already? How much ground?

305
00:20:12.753 --> 00:20:14.838
I think the chairman
was inspired by The Godfather,

306
00:20:15.422 --> 00:20:17.341
because he suddenly set up family lunches.

307
00:20:18.258 --> 00:20:19.259
-"Family lunches"?
-"Family lunches"?

308
00:20:19.343 --> 00:20:20.177
Yeah.

309
00:20:20.886 --> 00:20:24.223
He wants the whole family
to gather for lunch every Saturday.

310
00:20:24.973 --> 00:20:26.099
But guess who also joins.

311
00:20:29.186 --> 00:20:30.062
President Shin.

312
00:20:33.440 --> 00:20:34.900
You must have missed it, Ms. Hong.

313
00:20:34.983 --> 00:20:37.819
President Shin and Director Kang Nora
are getting engaged.

314
00:20:38.737 --> 00:20:42.115
The scales are now
tipping heavily in favor of

315
00:20:42.199 --> 00:20:43.408
my auntie and my future uncle.

316
00:20:44.993 --> 00:20:46.995
You need to try harder, Mr. Oh!

317
00:20:47.746 --> 00:20:48.664
Me?

318
00:20:49.331 --> 00:20:50.165
At what?

319
00:20:52.584 --> 00:20:55.045
Are you just going to
let her take everything?

320
00:20:55.128 --> 00:20:57.381
It was never mine to begin with.

321
00:20:58.423 --> 00:21:00.342
This stays between us three,

322
00:21:00.425 --> 00:21:02.135
but to describe my situation, it's like…

323
00:21:02.970 --> 00:21:04.263
Hangover soup without dried pollock,

324
00:21:04.346 --> 00:21:06.640
soybean paste stew without tofu,
and seaweed soup without beef.

325
00:21:09.393 --> 00:21:10.727
It'd be nice if I were included,

326
00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:12.980
but it wouldn't be upsetting if I weren't.

327
00:21:13.563 --> 00:21:16.525
Of course you should be upset
if it's intentional like that.

328
00:21:16.608 --> 00:21:19.778
If you move up the chain of command,
you'll gain authority over personnel.

329
00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:22.197
Then you could revive
the Risk Management Division

330
00:21:22.281 --> 00:21:24.741
and Mr. Bang Jin-mok
could return to the company!

331
00:21:24.825 --> 00:21:26.618
I wholeheartedly concur, Ms. Hong.

332
00:21:30.622 --> 00:21:33.083
You need to become
either the president or the chairman.

333
00:21:49.099 --> 00:21:52.019
Do you know why
I decided to stay at the company?

334
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:54.479
Like Mr. Bang said,

335
00:21:54.563 --> 00:21:57.232
I'd only be left with regrets
if I got forced out.

336
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.776
And there was also the promise I made you.

337
00:22:05.532 --> 00:22:06.408
On that note,

338
00:22:07.242 --> 00:22:08.910
wipe down the table.

339
00:22:28.889 --> 00:22:31.725
Chairman, we have
quite a spread for you today.

340
00:22:32.350 --> 00:22:35.062
No need for all that. My goodness.

341
00:22:38.774 --> 00:22:40.108
Seaweed is good for you.

342
00:22:44.404 --> 00:22:46.364
President Shin, eat up.

343
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:47.824
I will, thank you.

344
00:22:51.495 --> 00:22:53.121
To describe my situation, it's like…

345
00:22:54.122 --> 00:22:55.248
seaweed soup without beef.

346
00:22:56.416 --> 00:22:59.461
It'd be nice if I were included,
but it wouldn't be upsetting if I weren't.

347
00:22:59.961 --> 00:23:02.547
Of course you should be upset
if it's intentional like that.

348
00:23:05.759 --> 00:23:07.844
You must be enjoying work
in the Trading Division.

349
00:23:08.637 --> 00:23:10.097
It's nice to see you smiling.

350
00:23:12.015 --> 00:23:14.017
I'm not exactly thrilled
about my new division.

351
00:23:14.601 --> 00:23:15.894
But if I wasn't transferred,

352
00:23:15.977 --> 00:23:18.480
I would've never realized
how great my old team

353
00:23:19.564 --> 00:23:20.398
truly was.

354
00:23:22.025 --> 00:23:23.068
Did you hear that, sir?

355
00:23:23.902 --> 00:23:27.864
It sounds like our Albert is
finally realizing how vital personnel is

356
00:23:27.948 --> 00:23:31.660
and what role management must play
in an organization like ours.

357
00:23:32.702 --> 00:23:33.537
Is that so?

358
00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:35.789
That's a bit of a stretch.

359
00:23:35.872 --> 00:23:38.542
He's basically saying
it's tough for him to adjust,

360
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.168
even after being made a general manager.

361
00:23:40.252 --> 00:23:42.587
Well, someone's been made
a whole director.

362
00:23:42.671 --> 00:23:43.922
He's leagues ahead of that someone

363
00:23:44.005 --> 00:23:46.550
who does nothing
and doesn't know any better.

364
00:23:47.050 --> 00:23:48.468
Goodness.

365
00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:54.599
Perhaps we should've sent
our Nora to a division

366
00:23:54.683 --> 00:23:58.228
where she could socialize
with some colleagues.

367
00:23:59.146 --> 00:24:01.022
Ms. Song, look into that.

368
00:24:02.023 --> 00:24:03.150
Yes, sir. I'll look into it.

369
00:24:03.233 --> 00:24:04.484
Don't, Ms. Song.

370
00:24:05.861 --> 00:24:08.446
-Chairman.
-My word.

371
00:24:08.530 --> 00:24:10.740
I'm just trying to find her a good fit.

372
00:24:10.824 --> 00:24:13.160
Good luck finding that.

373
00:24:25.922 --> 00:24:28.216
-Did you enjoy the meal?
-Yes, I did.

374
00:24:29.050 --> 00:24:30.135
President Shin.

375
00:24:30.218 --> 00:24:31.178
You understand, right?

376
00:24:31.845 --> 00:24:33.805
It's all for my Nora's sake.

377
00:24:34.514 --> 00:24:38.101
Ma'am, you should refrain
from visiting the offices for now.

378
00:24:40.687 --> 00:24:41.688
Refrain?

379
00:24:41.771 --> 00:24:43.315
You want me to stay away?

380
00:24:43.398 --> 00:24:44.232
Yes.

381
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:46.234
The restructuring resulted
in massive layoffs,

382
00:24:46.318 --> 00:24:48.528
so the office isn't too thrilled
about welcoming

383
00:24:48.612 --> 00:24:50.655
the owner's daughter as a director.

384
00:24:50.739 --> 00:24:53.366
The appearance of
a succession battle taking center stage

385
00:24:53.450 --> 00:24:54.826
only fuels staff resentment.

386
00:24:54.910 --> 00:24:57.954
For the sake of the company's image,
please refrain for the time being.

387
00:24:58.788 --> 00:25:02.709
But Albert has Mr. Oh by his side
all day in the office.

388
00:25:03.877 --> 00:25:05.712
Who's going to look after my Nora?

389
00:25:05.795 --> 00:25:07.714
-I'm…
-I'll be sure

390
00:25:09.049 --> 00:25:10.217
to look after Nora.

391
00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:18.141
That would certainly put my mind at ease.

392
00:25:20.101 --> 00:25:21.228
Thank you.

393
00:25:21.770 --> 00:25:22.896
I'll see you next time.

394
00:25:23.480 --> 00:25:25.190
-You too…
-Goodbye.

395
00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:30.862
She can be so shy.

396
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:32.072
I wonder who she takes after.

397
00:25:34.241 --> 00:25:36.326
-Goodbye now.
-Take care, ma'am.

398
00:25:42.791 --> 00:25:45.794
BLOWOUT SALE
PROBIOTICS: 50 WON, GIMBAP: 1,000 WON

399
00:25:52.634 --> 00:25:54.010
-I'll take a roll of gimbap.
-Yes.

400
00:25:54.636 --> 00:25:55.470
That'll be 1,000 won.

401
00:25:56.471 --> 00:25:57.430
Thank you.

402
00:26:00.433 --> 00:26:03.186
Wow, you sound so different.

403
00:26:03.270 --> 00:26:04.813
"Thank you."

404
00:26:04.896 --> 00:26:06.189
I have to make a living.

405
00:26:09.109 --> 00:26:10.902
You didn't tell the others
about me, right?

406
00:26:10.986 --> 00:26:12.404
I didn't. You told me not to.

407
00:26:12.487 --> 00:26:13.530
Good.

408
00:26:19.661 --> 00:26:20.495
Mr. Bang.

409
00:26:22.455 --> 00:26:23.540
Should I become president?

410
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:28.169
You've suddenly turned into
a walking ball of ambition.

411
00:26:28.253 --> 00:26:31.506
If I moved up,
I'd gain authority over personnel,

412
00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:34.009
I could bring back Risk Management,

413
00:26:34.968 --> 00:26:36.219
and you could--

414
00:26:36.303 --> 00:26:37.679
-I'll take a roll of gimbap.
-Sure.

415
00:26:38.430 --> 00:26:40.265
That will be 1,000 won. There you go.

416
00:26:40.348 --> 00:26:41.349
Thank you!

417
00:26:43.601 --> 00:26:44.519
Ms. Hong told me

418
00:26:45.603 --> 00:26:49.399
she decided to stay at the company
because of what you said.

419
00:26:50.859 --> 00:26:52.277
She didn't want lingering regret.

420
00:26:53.194 --> 00:26:56.531
It probably has more to do with
what she wants than anything I said.

421
00:26:58.533 --> 00:27:00.535
Besides, stop coming here
to talk about work.

422
00:27:02.495 --> 00:27:03.663
You're my diary, Mr. Bang.

423
00:27:05.290 --> 00:27:07.125
Then buy all this for me, will you?

424
00:27:08.043 --> 00:27:09.127
How much is it?

425
00:27:09.210 --> 00:27:10.170
It's 5 for 50,000 won.

426
00:27:13.798 --> 00:27:14.632
Twenty thousand?

427
00:27:19.554 --> 00:27:20.722
I think it'd be best

428
00:27:20.805 --> 00:27:23.558
to use Yeouido Pirates
to shape public opinion.

429
00:27:23.641 --> 00:27:26.311
Unlike Ms. Song and Madam Choi,
who utilize the press,

430
00:27:26.394 --> 00:27:27.812
you can reach a younger demographic

431
00:27:27.896 --> 00:27:30.023
and deliver a stronger message
in cyberspace.

432
00:27:31.024 --> 00:27:32.609
After all, Yeouido Pirates is

433
00:27:32.692 --> 00:27:36.363
the number one source
for public opinions, intel, and rumors.

434
00:27:37.947 --> 00:27:38.990
"Yeouido Pirates"?

435
00:27:40.575 --> 00:27:41.701
What is that?

436
00:27:43.036 --> 00:27:43.953
You don't know?

437
00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:47.624
YEOUIDO PIRATES

438
00:27:47.707 --> 00:27:50.210
REGISTER NEW USER

439
00:27:53.630 --> 00:27:55.840
Nam Dong-gi, that punk.

440
00:27:56.674 --> 00:27:59.886
So this is what he was talking about,
the pirates, premium intel, or whatever?

441
00:27:59.969 --> 00:28:03.598
The thing is,
you need an invite to register.

442
00:28:04.182 --> 00:28:05.975
But I'll gladly use my one and only invite

443
00:28:06.559 --> 00:28:08.436
on you, sir.

444
00:28:12.774 --> 00:28:13.608
Done.

445
00:28:15.693 --> 00:28:16.736
-It's done?
-Yes, sir.

446
00:28:20.365 --> 00:28:21.199
What?

447
00:28:22.867 --> 00:28:24.494
Referral from "SexyGuy"?

448
00:28:24.577 --> 00:28:26.663
Oh, that's my username.

449
00:28:29.249 --> 00:28:32.043
It appears I've claimed your title
before you could.

450
00:28:34.838 --> 00:28:36.631
Jeez. Mr. Cha.

451
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:39.050
I get that it's
an anonymous forum and all,

452
00:28:39.134 --> 00:28:42.220
but you should still maintain
some class and act your age.

453
00:28:42.720 --> 00:28:43.805
Seriously, what is that?

454
00:28:44.764 --> 00:28:47.517
Jeez. Sexy, my foot.

455
00:28:49.644 --> 00:28:51.062
Let's see here.

456
00:28:53.189 --> 00:28:54.858
HANMIN CHAIRMAN'S EX-WIFE
HAS BEEN CAUSING A STIR IN YEOUIDO

457
00:28:54.941 --> 00:28:56.151
I SAW THAT WEIRD WOMAN TOO
WHO IS IT? A CELEBRITY?

458
00:28:56.234 --> 00:28:58.528
They know what they're talking about.

459
00:29:02.615 --> 00:29:06.119
Time to churn that rumor mill.

460
00:29:08.037 --> 00:29:14.002
"My peers in their twenties and thirties
are always talking

461
00:29:14.085 --> 00:29:18.173
so much smack about Nora's mama."

462
00:29:19.507 --> 00:29:21.509
"They say she's crass

463
00:29:21.593 --> 00:29:23.470
and flippant."

464
00:29:26.514 --> 00:29:27.390
Nice.

465
00:29:27.474 --> 00:29:28.933
YOUNGFIFTY: MY PEERS
IN THEIR TWENTIES AND THIRTIES…

466
00:29:30.727 --> 00:29:31.561
What's this?

467
00:29:31.644 --> 00:29:33.938
EXPOSING THE ALLEGED BACKROOM TIES
BETWEEN HANMIN AND DK VENTURES

468
00:29:34.022 --> 00:29:36.775
SOURCES CLAIM HANMIN AND DK'S TIES
GO BEYOND A SIMPLE INVESTMENT…

469
00:29:43.948 --> 00:29:46.910
President Shin,
have you heard of Yeouido Pirates?

470
00:29:51.164 --> 00:29:52.957
It's a cyber community that's considered

471
00:29:53.041 --> 00:29:56.461
the top source for public opinion
and sentiment in Yeouido.

472
00:29:57.128 --> 00:30:00.173
And someone posted
that scandalous allegation there.

473
00:30:00.256 --> 00:30:01.716
I thought it'd be best for me

474
00:30:02.342 --> 00:30:05.553
to discuss this matter with you,
before the chairman finds out about it.

475
00:30:07.597 --> 00:30:11.059
I mean, we can't have
such baseless claims going around.

476
00:30:11.935 --> 00:30:13.353
Perhaps it wasn't baseless,

477
00:30:13.436 --> 00:30:16.731
but written by a whistleblower
who knows something.

478
00:30:16.815 --> 00:30:18.399
It must be shut down without warning.

479
00:30:18.983 --> 00:30:23.363
Don't you think that'd make it
too obvious that we stepped in?

480
00:30:23.446 --> 00:30:26.366
You said it was the top source
for public sentiment.

481
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:28.034
There must be others lying in wait.

482
00:30:28.701 --> 00:30:31.204
We must give them a warning
and make an example.

483
00:30:34.624 --> 00:30:37.585
Do you know people at the Ministry
of Information and Communication?

484
00:30:38.753 --> 00:30:41.381
When it comes to government agencies,

485
00:30:41.464 --> 00:30:43.049
I have a direct line.

486
00:30:49.013 --> 00:30:52.517
I'll entrust you with
shutting down Yeouido Pirates then.

487
00:30:53.351 --> 00:30:55.353
Considering the seriousness of this task,

488
00:30:55.937 --> 00:30:59.983
I believe it would be best to have someone
as trustworthy as you handle this swiftly.

489
00:31:00.942 --> 00:31:03.611
I also lack knowledge
when it comes to domestic affairs.

490
00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:05.321
Don't worry.

491
00:31:05.405 --> 00:31:07.657
I can absolutely take care of it.

492
00:31:09.742 --> 00:31:14.163
Perhaps you'd like to join
and take a look before it's shut down?

493
00:31:14.998 --> 00:31:17.250
You need an invite to join,

494
00:31:17.333 --> 00:31:18.918
and I'll use my one and only--

495
00:31:19.002 --> 00:31:20.962
I'm fine.

496
00:31:23.172 --> 00:31:24.007
Okay.

497
00:31:46.195 --> 00:31:50.199
EXPOSING THE ALLEGED BACKROOM TIES
BETWEEN HANMIN AND DK VENTURES

498
00:32:04.213 --> 00:32:05.506
Any updates on Ms. Song?

499
00:32:06.132 --> 00:32:07.717
I don't think she knows yet.

500
00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:10.303
She's busy dealing with
that post on Yeouido Pirates.

501
00:32:10.845 --> 00:32:13.139
She'll be on your tail
once she realizes the funds are gone.

502
00:32:13.222 --> 00:32:15.433
Even with Kang Nora helping us out,

503
00:32:15.516 --> 00:32:18.102
the three of us aren't enough
to make a play for the 12th floor.

504
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:28.571
Let's stop here and split it in half,
fair and square.

505
00:32:29.155 --> 00:32:31.908
If we stop now,
we'll be nothing but thieves.

506
00:32:31.991 --> 00:32:35.119
Not at all.
We'll live our lives in riches.

507
00:32:35.703 --> 00:32:37.664
We can't stay in Korea anyway.

508
00:32:37.747 --> 00:32:39.207
Let's go to the US together,

509
00:32:39.290 --> 00:32:41.709
to Santa Monica Beach.

510
00:32:42.502 --> 00:32:45.672
Queen Bee, I've been meaning to tell you…

511
00:32:45.755 --> 00:32:46.965
Yes?

512
00:32:48.132 --> 00:32:49.342
Gwangalli Beach is nicer.

513
00:32:49.926 --> 00:32:51.511
Don't ruin my fantasy.

514
00:32:54.097 --> 00:32:57.350
Anyhow, I think
that "Captain" knows something.

515
00:32:57.433 --> 00:32:58.685
Who could it be?

516
00:33:03.272 --> 00:33:05.233
About President Shin…

517
00:33:07.318 --> 00:33:09.529
It seems he and the CEO of DK Ventures

518
00:33:10.154 --> 00:33:12.907
are unusually close.

519
00:33:12.991 --> 00:33:16.369
The CEO of DK does frequent the office,

520
00:33:16.452 --> 00:33:20.164
but I believe he's just seeking
investment advice on Korean companies.

521
00:33:23.084 --> 00:33:25.169
It appears that DK Ventures does,

522
00:33:25.253 --> 00:33:28.756
in fact, have ample cash reserves.

523
00:33:29.799 --> 00:33:30.758
Right.

524
00:33:31.551 --> 00:33:34.345
What does President Shin
get up to after work?

525
00:33:34.429 --> 00:33:40.101
I asked him to mentor Albert a while ago.

526
00:33:40.184 --> 00:33:42.020
I'd say he's gotten closer

527
00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:45.398
to Ms. Kang than to Albert.

528
00:33:46.816 --> 00:33:47.650
Is that so?

529
00:33:48.443 --> 00:33:52.780
Well, if that's what he has decided…

530
00:33:55.950 --> 00:33:56.784
Sir.

531
00:33:57.326 --> 00:34:00.496
We're receiving inquiries from politicians
who had specifically entrusted us

532
00:34:01.039 --> 00:34:02.373
with managing their funds.

533
00:34:04.125 --> 00:34:05.585
A Yeouido tabloid

534
00:34:06.544 --> 00:34:10.131
mentioned Hanmin in a list of companies
on the verge of bankruptcy.

535
00:34:12.258 --> 00:34:13.342
What the…

536
00:34:16.095 --> 00:34:18.347
Goodness.

537
00:34:19.265 --> 00:34:22.477
We'll need to do some client management.

538
00:34:27.857 --> 00:34:31.110
Busan Seagull

539
00:34:31.694 --> 00:34:34.739
-Busan Seagull
-Gwangalli Beach is nicer.

540
00:34:35.406 --> 00:34:38.201
Have you really forgotten--

541
00:34:39.494 --> 00:34:40.745
COMMUNITY
YEOUIDO NEWS

542
00:34:40.828 --> 00:34:42.747
Why can't I log in?

543
00:34:42.830 --> 00:34:44.749
Maybe you got banned
for writing something inappropriate?

544
00:34:44.832 --> 00:34:46.375
I only read posts nowadays.

545
00:34:53.466 --> 00:34:55.426
THIS WEBSITE HAS BEEN SHUT DOWN

546
00:34:55.510 --> 00:34:57.136
It's being shut down?

547
00:35:01.724 --> 00:35:03.351
You know Yeouido Pirates
has been shut down, right?

548
00:35:05.436 --> 00:35:06.813
This is an attack on the free press.

549
00:35:09.190 --> 00:35:10.566
We're talking about real people.

550
00:35:10.650 --> 00:35:12.944
They're behind those monitors,
on PC communications, and online.

551
00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:16.155
We must expose the perpetrator
behind that heinous deed and--

552
00:35:16.239 --> 00:35:17.782
My dad and President Shin did it.

553
00:35:19.033 --> 00:35:19.867
What?

554
00:35:20.701 --> 00:35:21.744
I see.

555
00:35:22.328 --> 00:35:25.039
When my dad saw a post
that was critical of both Hanmin and DK,

556
00:35:25.123 --> 00:35:27.500
he immediately made a call
and shut them down.

557
00:35:28.501 --> 00:35:30.128
It was upon
President Shin's special request.

558
00:35:30.211 --> 00:35:32.547
So President Shin ordered him to do it.

559
00:35:32.630 --> 00:35:35.299
Was it the post
that discussed the backroom ties

560
00:35:35.383 --> 00:35:36.217
between Hanmin and DK?

561
00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:38.719
They felt guilty because it's true.
That's why they shut it down.

562
00:35:39.595 --> 00:35:41.430
I will never forgive them.

563
00:35:44.016 --> 00:35:45.560
I get it, but let's eat for now.

564
00:35:46.060 --> 00:35:47.395
-Okay.
-Okay.

565
00:35:50.648 --> 00:35:52.692
That Captain definitely knows something.

566
00:35:57.822 --> 00:36:01.200
Yeouido Pirates is back
with a must-read announcement!

567
00:36:07.039 --> 00:36:08.499
The Captain posted a new announcement!

568
00:36:12.378 --> 00:36:14.130
"If you keep coming after us,

569
00:36:14.213 --> 00:36:17.216
we will expose the details
of Hanmin's slush fund."

570
00:36:18.134 --> 00:36:19.177
The slush fund?

571
00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:20.136
Hold on.

572
00:36:20.678 --> 00:36:23.931
"Pildong, general counsel, shell company."

573
00:36:24.599 --> 00:36:28.019
Pildong was a new law firm
that was established only last November,

574
00:36:28.853 --> 00:36:31.355
but they ended up
representing Chairman Kang.

575
00:36:31.439 --> 00:36:32.273
Why?

576
00:36:32.356 --> 00:36:34.066
Because its senior managing partner

577
00:36:34.150 --> 00:36:36.402
worked as general counsel
for Hanmin until October.

578
00:36:36.485 --> 00:36:38.988
Subsequently,
they were appointed as counsel

579
00:36:39.071 --> 00:36:40.823
for three well-capitalized
shell companies.

580
00:36:40.907 --> 00:36:43.993
We also suspect Hanmin
to be the source of their funds.

581
00:36:44.076 --> 00:36:45.286
Wait, I know this.

582
00:36:45.369 --> 00:36:46.704
This was what I was investigating.

583
00:36:46.787 --> 00:36:47.914
It's an insider.

584
00:36:48.539 --> 00:36:51.250
The Captain is someone inside Hanmin.

585
00:36:51.959 --> 00:36:55.755
What if they have
more up-to-date intel than our ledger?

586
00:36:58.174 --> 00:36:59.759
We must find them
and get them on our side.

587
00:37:00.635 --> 00:37:02.678
Because the enemy of my enemy is an ally?

588
00:37:19.904 --> 00:37:24.200
YEOUIDO PIRATES IS BACK
WITH A MUST-READ ANNOUNCEMENT!

589
00:37:25.785 --> 00:37:27.787
This "Captain"…

590
00:37:29.622 --> 00:37:30.790
I wonder what their deal is.

591
00:37:33.668 --> 00:37:37.964
You see, I checked it out
to monitor the situation,

592
00:37:38.047 --> 00:37:39.590
and it seems they're very well-informed.

593
00:37:40.299 --> 00:37:43.928
They might not be bluffing
about exposing our slush fund.

594
00:37:45.137 --> 00:37:47.932
What if they really do have
cards up their sleeve?

595
00:37:54.522 --> 00:37:56.357
The slush fund must be
quite a formidable amount.

596
00:37:57.275 --> 00:37:59.986
Yet you managed to safely avoid
the prosecutors' investigation.

597
00:38:00.736 --> 00:38:01.737
Well…

598
00:38:02.488 --> 00:38:04.615
I wouldn't know anything about that.

599
00:38:04.699 --> 00:38:07.743
Must we work so hard to preserve something
we know nothing about?

600
00:38:09.578 --> 00:38:10.454
Well…

601
00:38:11.247 --> 00:38:12.748
The slush fund…

602
00:38:13.332 --> 00:38:14.709
Ms. Song would know.

603
00:38:14.792 --> 00:38:16.377
She's always by his side, after all.

604
00:38:16.460 --> 00:38:17.336
I know nothing.

605
00:38:18.587 --> 00:38:21.549
First, we must find
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

606
00:38:21.632 --> 00:38:23.592
Right, we should.

607
00:38:23.676 --> 00:38:24.719
We must.

608
00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:25.636
Mr. Oh.

609
00:38:26.595 --> 00:38:27.555
I'll leave it to you again.

610
00:38:28.764 --> 00:38:30.850
Me? Again?

611
00:38:30.933 --> 00:38:34.103
You've been spearheading
the task up until now,

612
00:38:34.186 --> 00:38:36.230
so me taking over now would be a bit…

613
00:38:37.064 --> 00:38:39.108
It would be unideal, right?

614
00:38:39.191 --> 00:38:40.067
Probably.

615
00:38:40.151 --> 00:38:42.278
Right. I should handle it.

616
00:38:42.987 --> 00:38:44.030
-I'll take care of it.
-Yes.

617
00:38:46.324 --> 00:38:47.825
That jerk.

618
00:38:52.747 --> 00:38:53.956
Jeez, you scared me.

619
00:38:54.623 --> 00:38:57.585
Ms. Lee, tell Cha from Research
to come to my office immediately.

620
00:38:58.169 --> 00:38:59.420
And bring two cups of tea.

621
00:38:59.503 --> 00:39:00.504
Yes, sir.

622
00:39:04.717 --> 00:39:08.804
Maybe Executive Director Oh was provoked
by President Shin and Nora's engagement?

623
00:39:10.139 --> 00:39:12.808
He's become a total henchman
for the president.

624
00:39:12.892 --> 00:39:14.852
He keeps coming back with updates,

625
00:39:14.935 --> 00:39:17.646
and the president told him
to find the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

626
00:39:17.730 --> 00:39:18.939
See? I was right.

627
00:39:19.565 --> 00:39:21.233
We need to find them first.

628
00:39:24.153 --> 00:39:25.112
Could the Captain be

629
00:39:25.905 --> 00:39:27.073
the same person?

630
00:39:30.785 --> 00:39:34.246
The whistleblower who sent
the slush fund ledger to the president.

631
00:39:35.998 --> 00:39:38.167
I don't think so, because Yehppee is…

632
00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:43.381
See?

633
00:39:43.464 --> 00:39:45.174
You still don't trust me.

634
00:39:45.257 --> 00:39:48.177
It's not that.
It's just that I need to protect them.

635
00:39:49.345 --> 00:39:51.764
Well, although they abandoned me and left.

636
00:39:58.813 --> 00:39:59.939
ACCESS PROHIBITED

637
00:40:00.022 --> 00:40:01.357
ACCESS PERMITTED

638
00:40:01.440 --> 00:40:02.483
DISCUSSION BOARD

639
00:40:02.566 --> 00:40:03.401
Here's a preview.

640
00:40:03.484 --> 00:40:07.238
These are classified documents from Hanmin
for your reading pleasure.

641
00:40:07.321 --> 00:40:08.322
Roar.

642
00:40:08.406 --> 00:40:11.117
PREVIEW: CLASSIFIED DOCUMENTS
FROM HANMIN EXPOSED

643
00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:13.953
INTRANET DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT
IMPROVEMENT PROPOSAL

644
00:40:17.206 --> 00:40:19.250
We most certainly took care of it.

645
00:40:19.792 --> 00:40:22.503
But this document was only briefed today.

646
00:40:22.586 --> 00:40:26.132
It's a classified document
that only an insider would have access to.

647
00:40:26.215 --> 00:40:28.968
These jerks weren't bluffing.

648
00:40:30.094 --> 00:40:32.179
Should I report this to President Shin?

649
00:40:32.263 --> 00:40:34.557
That would only stir up trouble,
don't you think?

650
00:40:37.184 --> 00:40:38.018
What is it?

651
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:40.146
You suspect someone, don't you?

652
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:43.816
Well…

653
00:40:43.899 --> 00:40:45.234
If it wasn't an insider…

654
00:40:45.317 --> 00:40:46.152
Yes?

655
00:40:47.236 --> 00:40:50.281
An outsider must have done it?

656
00:40:54.952 --> 00:40:55.953
Are you saying

657
00:40:56.036 --> 00:40:58.539
that the whole country is a suspect?

658
00:41:01.292 --> 00:41:03.419
Perhaps you should consult
the head of the IT Division?

659
00:41:05.838 --> 00:41:06.672
Data systems.

660
00:41:07.256 --> 00:41:08.883
-Networks.
-Yes.

661
00:41:17.892 --> 00:41:19.935
Mr. Lee from the IT Division told me

662
00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:22.229
that Executive Director Oh
summoned the head of IT

663
00:41:22.313 --> 00:41:24.648
and asked who could've leaked
the classified document.

664
00:41:25.149 --> 00:41:28.569
Then he flipped out and ordered him
to see if there were signs of hacking.

665
00:41:28.652 --> 00:41:30.863
If it were a hacker,
they would've demanded money,

666
00:41:30.946 --> 00:41:31.822
not played mind games.

667
00:41:33.032 --> 00:41:35.534
That classified document
was the intranet improvement proposal.

668
00:41:35.618 --> 00:41:38.287
The president went straight
to Mr. Lee to take care of it,

669
00:41:38.370 --> 00:41:39.705
bypassing the head of IT.

670
00:41:40.289 --> 00:41:41.957
Lee Yong-gi produced it,

671
00:41:42.041 --> 00:41:45.503
and Albert Oh of Trading
and Cha Jung-il of Research were CC-ed.

672
00:41:45.586 --> 00:41:46.962
Shin Jung-woo was the recipient,

673
00:41:47.046 --> 00:41:49.298
and I also snuck a peek.

674
00:41:50.382 --> 00:41:53.135
Only those five people
had access to that document.

675
00:41:53.219 --> 00:41:56.305
Then those are
our five Captain candidates.

676
00:41:59.475 --> 00:42:00.309
It's not you, is it?

677
00:42:01.352 --> 00:42:02.561
Of course it's not me.

678
00:42:02.645 --> 00:42:04.688
Would I be here if I had such talents?

679
00:42:05.648 --> 00:42:06.482
What about Shin Jung-woo?

680
00:42:06.565 --> 00:42:07.816
It's not him, either.

681
00:42:07.900 --> 00:42:09.902
Yeouido Pirates was created a year ago.

682
00:42:11.487 --> 00:42:15.241
Mr. Lee was in the breakroom with me
when that post was uploaded,

683
00:42:15.324 --> 00:42:16.408
so he's ruled out.

684
00:42:17.993 --> 00:42:19.453
My gut tells me

685
00:42:19.537 --> 00:42:22.164
that Cha is perfectly capable
of such obnoxious cockiness.

686
00:42:22.748 --> 00:42:25.793
Gosh, I really hope it's not that jerk.

687
00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:31.674
Let's try leaking something else.

688
00:42:39.723 --> 00:42:40.724
Mr. Cha.

689
00:42:40.808 --> 00:42:42.393
Do you know what happens
when God gets angry?

690
00:42:44.520 --> 00:42:45.396
He gets cross.

691
00:42:46.605 --> 00:42:48.607
There are two primary Captain candidates.

692
00:42:49.358 --> 00:42:51.819
Albert Oh and Cha Jung-il.

693
00:42:59.868 --> 00:43:01.453
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

694
00:43:02.204 --> 00:43:03.038
Thank you.

695
00:43:11.797 --> 00:43:14.508
Make it seem like
it was mixed up at the copier,

696
00:43:14.592 --> 00:43:15.926
and the bait is cast.

697
00:43:16.010 --> 00:43:18.387
DOMESTIC SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK,
GLOBAL SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK

698
00:43:18.971 --> 00:43:21.056
Hot off the press,

699
00:43:21.140 --> 00:43:23.684
Hanmin's preliminary budget
for next year unveiled!

700
00:43:25.728 --> 00:43:27.813
1998 CONTINGENCY BUDGET PLAN

701
00:43:29.815 --> 00:43:32.735
HANMIN'S PRELIMINARY BUDGET
FOR NEXT YEAR UNVEILED!

702
00:43:32.818 --> 00:43:35.988
OPERATION COSTS, LABOR COSTS, EXPENSES…

703
00:43:36.071 --> 00:43:38.073
Do they match up? Do you know who it is?

704
00:43:39.742 --> 00:43:41.243
This punk…

705
00:43:49.543 --> 00:43:50.461
Let's get started.

706
00:44:09.063 --> 00:44:10.564
What are you doing?

707
00:44:18.697 --> 00:44:20.032
This won't take long.

708
00:44:20.115 --> 00:44:21.116
Try moving your hands.

709
00:44:23.911 --> 00:44:24.995
It doesn't hurt, right?

710
00:44:25.079 --> 00:44:26.997
This is for everyone's safety.

711
00:44:27.790 --> 00:44:29.583
Everyone in Research is gone for the day,

712
00:44:29.667 --> 00:44:31.877
and Mr. Lee can't come
because he's busy working overtime

713
00:44:31.960 --> 00:44:33.337
on the last leak by himself.

714
00:44:34.838 --> 00:44:37.049
Just do as we say, and you'll be fine.

715
00:44:41.387 --> 00:44:43.180
This sort of genre isn't my thing.

716
00:45:02.825 --> 00:45:04.410
I bought those noodles.

717
00:45:06.829 --> 00:45:08.580
You just need to answer my questions,

718
00:45:09.289 --> 00:45:11.291
Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

719
00:45:12.960 --> 00:45:14.670
What? Me?

720
00:45:14.753 --> 00:45:16.213
I'm the Captain?

721
00:45:16.296 --> 00:45:18.132
Yes. You.

722
00:45:19.258 --> 00:45:21.343
You seem overly confident
about that, Ms. Hong.

723
00:45:23.011 --> 00:45:24.221
How could I not be?

724
00:45:29.643 --> 00:45:31.854
GLOBAL SUPPLY AND DEMAND OUTLOOK

725
00:45:34.815 --> 00:45:36.984
1998 CONTINGENCY BUDGET PLAN

726
00:45:37.067 --> 00:45:38.444
Hanmin's confidential documents

727
00:45:38.527 --> 00:45:40.654
were consistently uploaded
to Yeouido Pirates.

728
00:45:42.906 --> 00:45:44.283
Based on that,

729
00:45:44.366 --> 00:45:47.453
we leaked next year's budget plan
to you and Mr. Cha Jung-il,

730
00:45:48.912 --> 00:45:50.873
our two Captain candidates.

731
00:45:55.085 --> 00:45:56.420
And today,

732
00:45:56.503 --> 00:46:01.800
a post appeared on Yeouido Pirates
with Hanmin's budget plan for next year.

733
00:46:01.884 --> 00:46:05.220
Sure. I think I saw
a budget plan or whatever.

734
00:46:05.304 --> 00:46:06.722
But I don't know how to read that.

735
00:46:06.805 --> 00:46:08.265
And why just me?

736
00:46:08.348 --> 00:46:10.642
Based on that logic,
Mr. Cha should be tied up next to me.

737
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:14.354
Because you were the one
who uploaded today's post.

738
00:46:14.438 --> 00:46:16.815
No, I didn't. I swear it wasn't me!

739
00:46:17.900 --> 00:46:19.276
It is you.

740
00:46:20.694 --> 00:46:22.821
We gave different reports to each suspect.

741
00:46:23.822 --> 00:46:25.866
The new post on Yeouido Pirates

742
00:46:25.949 --> 00:46:28.827
contained information
that was leaked to you alone.

743
00:46:28.911 --> 00:46:30.704
The numbers were different, you see.

744
00:46:34.750 --> 00:46:38.504
Come to think of it,
I was able to join Yeouido Pirates

745
00:46:39.296 --> 00:46:40.631
with your referral.

746
00:46:41.215 --> 00:46:42.090
Remember?

747
00:46:43.258 --> 00:46:44.635
Why didn't you ask me?

748
00:46:45.844 --> 00:46:47.721
-Pardon?
-For an invite to the Yeouido Pirates.

749
00:46:48.430 --> 00:46:49.306
I can do that for you.

750
00:46:54.353 --> 00:46:55.312
Really?

751
00:46:58.106 --> 00:46:59.066
You're right.

752
00:47:01.109 --> 00:47:02.861
I am the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

753
00:47:03.737 --> 00:47:04.571
Oh my.

754
00:47:05.280 --> 00:47:06.907
Why would the chairman's grandson
do such a thing?

755
00:47:06.990 --> 00:47:09.076
That's what I'd like to ask you two.

756
00:47:09.159 --> 00:47:11.620
Why would you two do something like this?

757
00:47:20.629 --> 00:47:22.422
Big Al. It's me, Yong-gi.

758
00:47:23.131 --> 00:47:24.591
You're in there, right?

759
00:47:24.675 --> 00:47:25.968
Let him in.

760
00:47:27.135 --> 00:47:28.804
He's my one and only crew member.

761
00:47:30.013 --> 00:47:31.557
Mr. Lee is a crew member?

762
00:47:33.058 --> 00:47:34.184
You two are accomplices?

763
00:47:51.827 --> 00:47:55.664
My dad found out I was in film school,
and he forced me to return to Korea.

764
00:48:00.961 --> 00:48:03.839
Watching movies all day
eventually got old.

765
00:48:09.052 --> 00:48:11.221
It felt like I'd been exiled
to an island called Yeouido.

766
00:48:13.682 --> 00:48:15.809
But some people around me
loved their jobs,

767
00:48:15.892 --> 00:48:17.686
like Uncle Myeong-hwi.

768
00:48:19.229 --> 00:48:21.523
I guess I wanted
to do something worthwhile.

769
00:48:24.026 --> 00:48:26.403
That's when Mr. Lee caught my eye.

770
00:48:27.738 --> 00:48:30.282
He was a genius hacker geek,
clearly ahead of his time.

771
00:48:31.867 --> 00:48:35.203
And I picked up top-tier insider intel
at home and at work.

772
00:48:35.746 --> 00:48:38.040
Since Mr. Lee was serious
about his cyber world,

773
00:48:38.123 --> 00:48:39.499
I proposed working together.

774
00:48:48.216 --> 00:48:49.343
OPERATION COMPLETE!

775
00:48:51.720 --> 00:48:52.679
YEOUIDO PIRATES

776
00:48:52.763 --> 00:48:56.141
-Is it done?
-Now, this is the main page.

777
00:48:57.476 --> 00:49:00.103
Try writing a post or something.

778
00:49:00.187 --> 00:49:01.104
-A post.
-Yeah.

779
00:49:02.481 --> 00:49:04.983
Let's enter the discussion board…

780
00:49:05.817 --> 00:49:06.985
We need a title.

781
00:49:08.278 --> 00:49:09.363
"It's finally here."

782
00:49:10.656 --> 00:49:14.368
"Introducing Yeouido Pirates,
the complete intel collection of Yeouido."

783
00:49:14.868 --> 00:49:15.869
DISCUSSION BOARD

784
00:49:16.536 --> 00:49:20.540
"We look forward to a vibrant
and active community of members."

785
00:49:20.624 --> 00:49:21.958
PUBLISH

786
00:49:24.628 --> 00:49:25.462
Ta-da.

787
00:49:27.339 --> 00:49:28.215
It's done.

788
00:49:29.257 --> 00:49:30.926
-It's up.
-Wow, this is…

789
00:49:31.009 --> 00:49:32.302
We did it.

790
00:49:34.221 --> 00:49:35.847
You're the Captain now.

791
00:49:40.811 --> 00:49:44.564
Here, the members
can freely post whatever they wish.

792
00:49:48.735 --> 00:49:50.570
How did Big Al convince you?

793
00:49:52.572 --> 00:49:55.158
"Let's become a band of pirates
that sails the sea of information."

794
00:49:55.242 --> 00:49:57.536
"Let's democratize access
to monopolized information."

795
00:49:58.036 --> 00:50:00.038
"Let's make a world
where the people of Yeouido

796
00:50:00.122 --> 00:50:01.998
can call a spade a spade without fear."

797
00:50:07.045 --> 00:50:08.547
How grandiose.

798
00:50:09.214 --> 00:50:11.925
There was a reason
why you two were attached at the hip.

799
00:50:12.426 --> 00:50:15.846
That's why you met up here after work,
even after the restructuring.

800
00:50:16.430 --> 00:50:18.056
Why are you digging into Yeouido Pirates?

801
00:50:19.224 --> 00:50:20.350
Did Ms. Song put you up to it?

802
00:50:21.476 --> 00:50:22.728
Maybe my dad?

803
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:24.980
Or maybe President Shin?

804
00:50:25.063 --> 00:50:27.482
As if we'd tie someone up
because someone ordered us to.

805
00:50:28.066 --> 00:50:30.152
Then why are you doing this?

806
00:50:30.235 --> 00:50:34.114
President Shin and Executive Director Oh
are looking for the Captain.

807
00:50:34.197 --> 00:50:37.159
We found you first before things got ugly.

808
00:50:37.242 --> 00:50:38.410
Why?

809
00:50:40.495 --> 00:50:41.997
We're hoping to make a deal.

810
00:50:42.497 --> 00:50:44.332
You said in a post on Yeouido Pirates

811
00:50:45.333 --> 00:50:47.419
that you'd expose the slush fund
if provoked further.

812
00:50:50.839 --> 00:50:52.007
What's this now?

813
00:50:52.090 --> 00:50:54.009
What's with that sigh?

814
00:50:54.092 --> 00:50:55.969
Regarding the slush fund's size
and whereabouts…

815
00:50:58.346 --> 00:50:59.181
we know nothing.

816
00:51:00.515 --> 00:51:03.226
We just reworked what Uncle Myeong-hwi
let slip when he was drunk.

817
00:51:03.310 --> 00:51:05.437
They kept coming after us,
so we swung big.

818
00:51:06.646 --> 00:51:08.732
Can you untie me now?

819
00:51:10.609 --> 00:51:12.027
Untie me!

820
00:51:21.912 --> 00:51:25.373
They wouldn't tell on us, would they?

821
00:51:26.041 --> 00:51:27.876
Who would they tell, and about what?

822
00:51:27.959 --> 00:51:29.252
We asked about the slush fund.

823
00:51:30.128 --> 00:51:31.755
But nothing about stealing it, right?

824
00:51:32.506 --> 00:51:35.342
If anything, they're the ones
shaking in their boots.

825
00:51:41.890 --> 00:51:44.851
Ms. Hong and Ms. Go
wouldn't tell on us, right?

826
00:51:45.435 --> 00:51:46.645
Of course not.

827
00:51:46.728 --> 00:51:49.064
Then why did they ask
about the slush fund?

828
00:52:01.368 --> 00:52:03.912
I'll go back and ask Ms. Hong about it.

829
00:52:03.995 --> 00:52:04.955
No, don't.

830
00:52:05.497 --> 00:52:06.665
Go home. I'll see you tomorrow.

831
00:52:07.916 --> 00:52:08.750
Okay.

832
00:52:10.293 --> 00:52:11.253
Have a good night.

833
00:52:47.747 --> 00:52:48.790
It's been a while,

834
00:52:48.874 --> 00:52:50.000
Mr. Auto Repair Shop.

835
00:53:05.432 --> 00:53:06.433
That hurts.

836
00:53:06.892 --> 00:53:09.477
Let's talk this out, all right?

837
00:53:09.561 --> 00:53:11.354
At least tell me what you want.

838
00:53:16.026 --> 00:53:16.902
Hong Keum-bo.

839
00:53:17.444 --> 00:53:18.278
Hong Keum-bo?

840
00:53:18.361 --> 00:53:20.238
The woman you came with
to my auto repair shop.

841
00:53:20.322 --> 00:53:22.115
Just tell me how you know her.

842
00:53:34.836 --> 00:53:38.131
Do you think I could go
to a birthday party I wasn't invited to?

843
00:53:38.214 --> 00:53:41.092
To be precise,
another friend did invite me.

844
00:53:41.176 --> 00:53:42.469
When's their birthday?

845
00:53:42.552 --> 00:53:44.763
It's December 24th, on Christmas Eve.

846
00:53:46.431 --> 00:53:49.184
Is it your former roommate's birthday?

847
00:53:49.851 --> 00:53:51.061
How did you know?

848
00:53:53.104 --> 00:53:55.941
You mentioned you didn't have
many friends in Seoul.

849
00:53:57.943 --> 00:54:00.612
You remembered that?

850
00:54:02.322 --> 00:54:03.406
Yes, well…

851
00:54:04.407 --> 00:54:06.618
I would've forgotten
if it hadn't been a special day,

852
00:54:07.202 --> 00:54:09.871
but someone I dated long ago
was also born on December 24th.

853
00:54:11.581 --> 00:54:13.458
Whenever Christmas carols
played in the streets,

854
00:54:13.541 --> 00:54:16.002
she'd say it was like
a preview of her birthday.

855
00:54:28.640 --> 00:54:31.059
Let's help the less fortunate!

856
00:54:33.812 --> 00:54:36.189
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

857
00:54:36.272 --> 00:54:38.108
-Merry Christmas.
-Thank you.

858
00:54:38.191 --> 00:54:39.693
-Take care.
-Goodbye.

859
00:54:39.776 --> 00:54:42.112
-A sleighing song tonight
-A sleighing song tonight

860
00:54:45.031 --> 00:54:48.118
CLOSED ON THE 24TH FOR OUR DAUGHTER
25TH FOR BABY JESUS

861
00:54:51.705 --> 00:54:55.166
ULLALA CHICKEN

862
00:55:17.772 --> 00:55:20.650
Ma'am, this is
way too much food for just us.

863
00:55:20.734 --> 00:55:22.193
Not at all.

864
00:55:23.862 --> 00:55:25.697
-Take the leftovers home.
-Okay.

865
00:55:25.780 --> 00:55:28.116
Honey, you packed the kimchi
and ginseng chicken soup, right?

866
00:55:28.199 --> 00:55:30.452
Of course I did.

867
00:55:30.535 --> 00:55:33.872
Bom, Grandma and I are going
to the nursing home to volunteer,

868
00:55:33.955 --> 00:55:35.498
so have fun with your aunties, okay?

869
00:55:35.582 --> 00:55:36.499
Okay!

870
00:55:40.170 --> 00:55:41.337
Auntie!

871
00:55:48.178 --> 00:55:50.013
Let me check your invitations.

872
00:55:54.934 --> 00:55:58.313
HONG KEUM-BO'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY INVITATION

873
00:56:06.321 --> 00:56:07.447
Here you go.

874
00:56:07.530 --> 00:56:09.074
Thank you!

875
00:56:09.157 --> 00:56:10.033
It's Christmas Eve.

876
00:56:10.742 --> 00:56:12.202
Don't you have a date with the president?

877
00:56:12.285 --> 00:56:14.120
He said he had important plans today.

878
00:56:14.954 --> 00:56:16.581
That's suspicious.

879
00:56:16.664 --> 00:56:18.750
Could he have another woman?

880
00:56:19.542 --> 00:56:23.338
You know, like his first love,
an ex-girlfriend, or a secret lover?

881
00:56:24.339 --> 00:56:25.173
And what if

882
00:56:26.132 --> 00:56:27.634
she's someone we know?

883
00:56:33.139 --> 00:56:34.766
Someone at the president's level…

884
00:56:35.767 --> 00:56:37.143
would probably date an actress, right?

885
00:56:38.561 --> 00:56:39.687
Maybe Shim Eun-ha from The Last Match?

886
00:56:39.771 --> 00:56:41.231
Or Kim Hee-seon from Propose?

887
00:56:42.690 --> 00:56:44.609
Jeez, I'm just kidding.

888
00:56:45.568 --> 00:56:47.654
How many candles do you want? All 35?

889
00:56:48.404 --> 00:56:49.823
Just one.

890
00:56:50.490 --> 00:56:52.659
Is it her first birthday or something?
Right, Bom?

891
00:56:57.288 --> 00:56:59.207
Sure, it's not like it costs extra.

892
00:57:02.585 --> 00:57:03.503
Pink?

893
00:57:11.970 --> 00:57:13.012
Okay.

894
00:57:13.096 --> 00:57:16.182
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

895
00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:19.185
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

896
00:57:19.269 --> 00:57:21.688
-Happy birthday, dear Ms. Hong
-Happy birthday

897
00:57:21.771 --> 00:57:23.565
-Dear Hong Keum-bo
-Dear Auntie Jang-mi

898
00:57:23.648 --> 00:57:26.943
-Happy birthday to you
-Happy birthday to you

899
00:57:34.576 --> 00:57:35.410
Good job.

900
00:57:38.788 --> 00:57:39.789
Ta-da!

901
00:57:40.331 --> 00:57:42.208
I wanted us to watch it together.

902
00:57:42.292 --> 00:57:45.086
They're videos I took
when we were living in the dorms.

903
00:58:12.822 --> 00:58:13.907
Did you buy that camcorder?

904
00:58:14.407 --> 00:58:15.700
It looks really expensive.

905
00:58:17.243 --> 00:58:18.453
Jang-mi!

906
00:58:19.537 --> 00:58:20.788
What are you doing?

907
00:58:24.375 --> 00:58:25.376
Cucumber.

908
00:58:25.460 --> 00:58:27.378
-Cucumber.
-Cucumber.

909
00:58:30.423 --> 00:58:31.883
Congratulations!

910
00:58:37.597 --> 00:58:38.765
Have some. It's good.

911
00:58:40.517 --> 00:58:41.476
Is it good?

912
00:58:42.894 --> 00:58:44.062
It's so sour.

913
00:58:44.854 --> 00:58:46.940
-Ta-da.
-Can you do it?

914
00:58:54.656 --> 00:58:56.282
-Smile.
-Smile.

915
00:59:00.495 --> 00:59:02.664
Look over here, Bom. Isn't that so cool?

916
00:59:03.164 --> 00:59:04.541
Look at that!

917
00:59:07.669 --> 00:59:08.586
It's not easy.

918
00:59:08.670 --> 00:59:11.381
You broke it!

919
00:59:11.464 --> 00:59:14.259
It's okay. It's nothing to cry about.

920
00:59:14.801 --> 00:59:15.843
Sorry.

921
00:59:16.427 --> 00:59:19.430
My goodness. Should we try again, Bom?

922
00:59:19.514 --> 00:59:21.182
Do you want a taste?

923
00:59:21.266 --> 00:59:23.893
Isn't it so good?

924
00:59:24.519 --> 00:59:25.728
It's good, isn't it?

925
00:59:27.063 --> 00:59:28.022
Let's have some more.

926
00:59:30.733 --> 00:59:33.403
Hey, turn on the TV or play some music.

927
00:59:34.737 --> 00:59:35.905
Let's play some Christmas carols.

928
00:59:38.408 --> 00:59:39.242
I'm in.

929
00:59:39.325 --> 00:59:41.411
Whenever Christmas carols
play in the streets,

930
00:59:41.494 --> 00:59:43.371
it's like a preview of my birthday.

931
00:59:45.498 --> 00:59:48.418
Someone I dated long ago
was also born on December 24th.

932
00:59:49.752 --> 00:59:51.462
Whenever Christmas carols
played in the streets,

933
00:59:52.046 --> 00:59:54.215
she'd say it was like
a preview of her birthday.

934
00:59:58.803 --> 01:00:00.013
We're closed today.

935
01:00:15.695 --> 01:00:16.779
It's so cold.

936
01:00:19.782 --> 01:00:21.659
What happened to your lips?

937
01:00:25.330 --> 01:00:27.248
How did you know about my parents' place?

938
01:00:27.332 --> 01:00:29.792
Wait, are you here to pick up your aunt?

939
01:00:29.876 --> 01:00:32.253
Aunt Nora and I aren't even that close.

940
01:00:34.005 --> 01:00:36.132
But you two are much closer
than I expected.

941
01:00:37.842 --> 01:00:39.218
We're not that close.

942
01:00:43.306 --> 01:00:44.641
You didn't tell anyone, did you?

943
01:00:46.100 --> 01:00:48.311
That I'm the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

944
01:00:49.687 --> 01:00:50.730
I didn't.

945
01:00:51.522 --> 01:00:53.274
Then I'll keep your secret too.

946
01:00:55.360 --> 01:00:57.403
Inspector of the Capital Market
Investigation Division at the FSS…

947
01:00:59.614 --> 01:01:00.865
Hong Keum-bo.

948
01:01:15.922 --> 01:01:16.964
When did you find out?

949
01:01:18.174 --> 01:01:19.967
It doesn't seem like
you feigned ignorance.

950
01:01:20.551 --> 01:01:21.761
Remember Horang Auto Repair Shop?

951
01:01:23.221 --> 01:01:25.181
A few days ago, I ran into that scary man

952
01:01:25.807 --> 01:01:27.100
in front of our office building.

953
01:01:28.893 --> 01:01:30.269
He asked about Hong Keum-bo.

954
01:01:33.606 --> 01:01:34.649
Hong Keum-bo.

955
01:01:35.566 --> 01:01:36.401
Hong Keum-bo?

956
01:01:36.484 --> 01:01:38.361
The woman you came with
to my auto repair shop.

957
01:01:39.737 --> 01:01:41.322
Just tell me how you know her.

958
01:01:53.918 --> 01:01:55.795
Fine, I'll tell you!

959
01:01:55.878 --> 01:01:56.754
I will tell you!

960
01:02:00.174 --> 01:02:01.342
That pretty highway ghost?

961
01:02:02.260 --> 01:02:03.469
I haven't seen her since.

962
01:02:04.679 --> 01:02:06.264
I'm telling you the truth!

963
01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:08.141
She told me to just go home

964
01:02:08.224 --> 01:02:10.393
if I didn't want to get beaten up
in some random place!

965
01:02:10.476 --> 01:02:11.561
Sir.

966
01:02:16.315 --> 01:02:17.984
Damn it, that seriously hurts.

967
01:02:18.484 --> 01:02:20.194
Why are you so violent?

968
01:02:21.112 --> 01:02:22.655
He says he doesn't know her.

969
01:02:25.616 --> 01:02:28.327
Hong Keum-bo might've acted alone.

970
01:02:31.038 --> 01:02:32.749
What should I do with the boy?

971
01:02:32.832 --> 01:02:34.417
Let Albert go for now.

972
01:02:51.267 --> 01:02:52.268
Hong Keum-bo.

973
01:02:55.354 --> 01:02:56.439
"HONG KEUM-BO" SEARCH RESULTS

974
01:02:58.524 --> 01:03:01.360
HONG KEUM-BO, THE FSS WITCH OF YEOUIDO…

975
01:03:03.237 --> 01:03:04.530
SHE LOOKED INTO HANMIN'S SLUSH FUND…

976
01:03:04.614 --> 01:03:06.949
"Hanmin's slush fund"?

977
01:03:07.742 --> 01:03:09.577
You said in a post on Yeouido Pirates

978
01:03:10.578 --> 01:03:12.663
that you'd expose the slush fund
if provoked further.

979
01:03:12.747 --> 01:03:14.665
Regarding the slush fund's size
and whereabouts…

980
01:03:15.541 --> 01:03:16.375
we know nothing.

981
01:03:26.761 --> 01:03:28.137
I'm looking for someone,

982
01:03:28.221 --> 01:03:30.640
and I need a clear picture of her face.

983
01:03:51.369 --> 01:03:52.912
1989 FSS NEW HIRE TRAINING CENTER

984
01:03:58.376 --> 01:03:59.752
After Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident,

985
01:04:00.336 --> 01:04:03.798
I once overheard Ms. Song
and my grandfather talking.

986
01:04:04.382 --> 01:04:07.176
And the demoted FSS inspector
they mentioned then

987
01:04:08.636 --> 01:04:10.221
lied to get a job in my division?

988
01:04:12.640 --> 01:04:15.101
Did you tie me to a chair
and ask about the slush fund

989
01:04:15.184 --> 01:04:16.435
as part of your undercover operation?

990
01:04:17.854 --> 01:04:18.688
That's right.

991
01:04:19.272 --> 01:04:20.648
I was doing my job the whole time.

992
01:04:24.277 --> 01:04:26.362
It's too dangerous for you
to continue working at Hanmin.

993
01:04:28.447 --> 01:04:30.783
Danger and disappointment
can't be reasons for me to give up.

994
01:04:32.201 --> 01:04:33.744
There's a job I must finish.

995
01:04:36.831 --> 01:04:38.958
I knew Hong Keum-bo
wouldn't listen, either.

996
01:04:42.336 --> 01:04:44.130
I'm not sure if you'd accept this deal,

997
01:04:45.172 --> 01:04:48.593
but you can't be exposed
as the Captain of Yeouido Pirates either.

998
01:04:50.344 --> 01:04:52.013
Forget being the successor,

999
01:04:52.096 --> 01:04:53.598
you'd be disowned.

1000
01:04:55.433 --> 01:04:56.851
So how about we both feign ignorance?

1001
01:04:58.227 --> 01:04:59.896
I don't want to feign ignorance.

1002
01:04:59.979 --> 01:05:01.188
I still think

1003
01:05:02.023 --> 01:05:04.108
we're on the same team.

1004
01:05:08.446 --> 01:05:09.947
Don't you need me for your operation?

1005
01:05:11.198 --> 01:05:12.491
Of course, it won't be for free.

1006
01:05:14.410 --> 01:05:16.120
Do you even know what I'm after?

1007
01:05:17.747 --> 01:05:20.124
Would you be willing to turn over
your entire share in Hanmin

1008
01:05:20.708 --> 01:05:22.001
to me?

1009
01:05:24.795 --> 01:05:25.630
If you'd like.

1010
01:05:26.213 --> 01:05:27.089
In return,

1011
01:05:28.007 --> 01:05:30.635
I need to find the culprit who instigated
Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident.

1012
01:06:09.882 --> 01:06:13.469
A lady invites you to dinner,
and you bring toilet paper?

1013
01:06:13.552 --> 01:06:15.972
It's the best housewarming gift.

1014
01:06:17.682 --> 01:06:20.559
Also, the Ms. Hong I know
is incredibly practical.

1015
01:06:22.853 --> 01:06:24.689
We should've asked Mr. Bang to join.

1016
01:06:28.776 --> 01:06:30.444
He wouldn't be able to handle the truth.

1017
01:06:32.196 --> 01:06:33.030
What truth?

1018
01:06:34.865 --> 01:06:35.908
Mr. Lee.

1019
01:06:37.034 --> 01:06:38.077
Take a deep breath with me.

1020
01:06:38.619 --> 01:06:39.453
Inhale deeply.

1021
01:06:40.579 --> 01:06:41.622
Exhale deeply.

1022
01:06:43.916 --> 01:06:45.209
1989 FSS NEW HIRE TRAINING CENTER

1023
01:06:48.546 --> 01:06:49.839
You're with the FSS?

1024
01:06:50.381 --> 01:06:52.341
I resigned, so not anymore.

1025
01:06:53.217 --> 01:06:54.385
And you're older…

1026
01:06:54.468 --> 01:06:55.636
Yes, she is.

1027
01:06:58.431 --> 01:07:00.725
Mr. Lee, you look like
you have a lot of questions.

1028
01:07:01.308 --> 01:07:03.227
I do, but I can wait.

1029
01:07:03.310 --> 01:07:04.186
Just come and sit.

1030
01:07:10.860 --> 01:07:12.737
I'll get right to the point.

1031
01:07:12.820 --> 01:07:15.448
This is what Uncle Myeong-hwi compiled
to blow the whistle with…

1032
01:07:15.531 --> 01:07:16.949
It's the slush fund ledger.

1033
01:07:17.033 --> 01:07:19.452
The FSS does not want to investigate,

1034
01:07:19.535 --> 01:07:22.038
and Hanmin is being targeted
by both internal and external forces.

1035
01:07:22.121 --> 01:07:23.664
You mean DK Ventures and President Shin?

1036
01:07:24.248 --> 01:07:25.458
We figured out as much.

1037
01:07:25.958 --> 01:07:28.627
Our ultimate goal is to
steal the slush fund, buy up the stock,

1038
01:07:28.711 --> 01:07:31.213
and become the major shareholder
to protect the company.

1039
01:07:35.801 --> 01:07:38.429
Our first target is
the domestic slush funds.

1040
01:07:39.930 --> 01:07:40.765
Who manages them?

1041
01:07:46.312 --> 01:07:47.313
DOMESTIC SLUSH FUNDS

1042
01:07:47.396 --> 01:07:49.148
"Managed by Executive Director
Oh Deok-gyu?"

1043
01:07:50.649 --> 01:07:51.484
My dad?

1044
01:08:34.193 --> 01:08:36.028
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

1045
01:08:36.737 --> 01:08:38.697
You keep so many secrets from me, Dad.

1046
01:08:39.365 --> 01:08:41.325
If I become the successor,
it won't be an issue.

1047
01:08:41.867 --> 01:08:43.661
Have you heard of the old banknote scam?

1048
01:08:44.161 --> 01:08:47.248
-Hong!
-I need the rumor to spread like wildfire.

1049
01:08:47.331 --> 01:08:49.333
This must stay between us.

1050
01:08:49.834 --> 01:08:52.253
Why take such a big gamble, Big Al?

1051
01:08:52.336 --> 01:08:54.213
How can we know you're serious?

1052
01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:55.673
Do you know who I am, punk?

1053
01:08:56.590 --> 01:08:59.343
Reality is definitely different
from what I anticipated.

1054
01:09:00.094 --> 01:09:01.512
Let's go for it. Let's do it.

1055
01:09:01.595 --> 01:09:02.888
This is Song Ju-ran.

1056
01:09:02.972 --> 01:09:04.306
Can you check on something for me?

1057
01:09:05.015 --> 01:09:05.850
Let's get started.

1058
01:09:08.060 --> 01:09:13.065
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim

